	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A brother of Q. Curtius Salassus, probably an officer under Cn. Pompeius (32) in Spain in 45 when he plotted to capture his commander and bring him to Caesar. He was discovered and put to death (Cic. Fam. 6.18.2; on the cognomen, see CIL 9.326, 327).\n" .
